column2: mRNA profiling in rectus abdominis muscle from patients with upper GI cancer

Rectus abdominis muscle biopsies were obtained from 65 upper gastrointestinal (UGI) cancer patients during open surgery and RNA profiling was performed on a subset of this cohort (n=21) using the Affymetrix U133+2 platform with the aim of identifying biomarkers of cancer related muscle wasting.
N = 21 (18 UGI cancer; 3 non cancer surgery)
Faculty of Health Sciences and Sport
Room 4B133 Cottrell Building, University of Stirling, Airthrey Road

Stephens NA, Gallagher IJ, Rooyackers O, Skipworth RJ, Tan BH, Marstrand T, Ross JA, Guttridge DC, Lundell L, Fearon KC, Timmons JA. Using transcriptomics to identify and validate novel biomarkers of human skeletal muscle cancer cachexia. Genome Medicine, 2:1, Jan 2010. DOI:10.1186/gm122

Muscle was homogenized in Trizol with a Mini-Beadbeater-8 homogenizer and RNA extraction carried out using Trizol protocol (Invitrogen). Hybridization, washing, staining and scanning of the arrays were performed according to manufacturer's instructions (Affymetrix).
